                        <div class="lesson-content">
                            
<h3>Authentication Logging</h3>
<p>Authentication logging can be very useful to look at if you are having issues logging in. </p>
<p><b>/var/log/auth.log</b></p>
<p>This contains system authorization logs, such as user login and the authentication method used. </p>
<p>Sample snippet:</p>
<pre>
Jan 31 10:37:50 icebox pkexec: pam_unix(polkit-1:session): session opened for user root by (uid=1000)
</pre>

                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-md-6 practice">
                        <div class="exercise-content">
                            <h3>Exercise</h3>
<p>Do some failed logins and then a successful one, look at your /var/log/auth.log and see what happened.</p>

                        </div>

                        <div class="quiz-content">
                            <h3>Quiz Question</h3>
<p>What log is used for user authentication?</p>
<h3>Quiz Answer</h3>
<p>auth.log</p>
</div>

                        </div>
                    </div>

